title: [Tavern Burrow, Pilsner Avenue]
description: A small niche has been carved into an old stone wall fronting the street.  Dried flowers and small folded notes surround the opening.  A young woman kneels before the wall, a wedding bouquet in one hand.  The other presses against the wall so hard that its fingertips have whitened.
